4.02/5  rDev -9.7%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Poured from a can into a snifter glass.  I got this in a trade from crowlcrowlcrowl. 
L:  A medium golden color with lacing that quickly recedes.  The beer started off cloudy on the pour until a giant gob of yeast plopped out, then it got really murky and cloudy. 
S:  Very tropical with mango, pineapple, apricot and some huge dank smells.  
T:  Tropical fruit flavors with mango, pineapple and some stone fruit like peach and apricot.  Some huge candy fruit sweetness then mixes with some huge dank resinous flavors.  Weed, pine and bitterness finishes it out with some alcohol.  
M:  Full, coating, bitter, alcohol and super resiny.  
O:  A really good beer by Grimm.  This is my second beer from them and I have not been let down one bit.  Great beers. 761 charactersKadonny, Oct 16, 2016
