4.06/5  rDev -8.8%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 3.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4A very interesting brew. I had it first on tap in Brooklyn, and then again tonight from a can at a pizza joint near Union Square. Poured from a can dated 3/8/16 into a Teku glass.
Look: Gorgeous. Super turbid/hazy/whatever, beautiful dark amber color with a nice pillowy head
Smell: Smells interesting. Kind of fruity.
Taste: Not what I expect from a DIPA, it's almost... Saison-y. It's got a sharpness to it with very little hop bitterness to it. Slightly tart, very unique and interesting beer. I like it. Don't love it, but I like it.
Feel: Great, pillowy mouthfeel
Overall: A DIPA unlike any I've ever had. Very unique beer drinking experience. 649 charactersDeweyCheatem-n-Howe, Apr 27, 2016
