Quite bitter and lemony, with an earthy spiciness that hints at Belgian yeast and lingers enticingly. Some (okay, kind of a lot) of sweet wheat. Herbal finish. On the sweeter, juicier side of DIPAs. 
Thick and fun. 
Good, but not quite great. Nearly though! 465 charactersAgentMunky, Oct 16, 2015
