4.47/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5On draft, NYC, 37F, 12 ounce fluted tulip snifter.
Nose aroma is special. Refined, balanced and mathematical.
Texture isn't too light, but also not very heavy for an 8.0% abv ale. Triple beam malts and hops here.
Taste is definitely equisite, but for this style of hop blend (nelsony and simcoey), its not the best, but very close to it. Plenty of fruity notes, followed by organic two row pungencey, followed by dank hops. Pretty amazing in terms of whats availible in the North East tri state market, still not as complex or flavorful as  Grey Sail, Singlecut, or Other Half.
Afterimage, while it is an amazing product (definitely seek it out) it tasted very similar to Grey Sail Captains Daughter, which I preferred more, mainly because of the more extreme malt presence and dry hop schedule.
Very impressed with Grimm Artisanal ales. Seriously top notch, and they certainly have a Vermont and Massachussets juicy cloudy IPA influence, but I think that Other Half, Grey Sail and Singlecut do it slightly better in terms of IPA's. 
Cannot wait to try some of their imperial stouts.
I will also mention that I think their bottle and can art and graphic design is absolutely amazing. Inspired by the 80's sci-fi generation of Automan, V, and Predator. 
A+ for the design people behind the logos and label artwork. 1,321 characterspinyin, Oct 03, 2015
