4.94/5  rDev +11%look: 4 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Had this on tap, but now it's time for a formal review.  16 oz. can into a tulip.
A - Looks like a standard East coast IPA.  A wheat-colored yellow/orange with a bubbly off-white head that's not going anywhere.  It's glowing!
N - Smell this one from a mile away.  Bright, juicy hops with very little bitterness.  Lots of citrus and pine.  Very pungent and inviting.
T - Yeah, so much like the nose.  Plenty of juicy hops, but absolutely no bitterness.  It's all juice.  Most impressively the flavor is tremendous, but the finish is squeaky clean.  A thirst-quenching IPA with absolutely no alcohol.
M - Just what I love; immediate froth.  No liquid whatsoever by the time it hits my tongue.  It's like drinking hoppy cotton candy.
O - An impressive offering from Grimm.  Better than their sours as far as I'm concerned. 824 charactersCraftFan5, Sep 25, 2015
